                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/3–2751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation to the
                        Torquay Conference</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Corse</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Torquay</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-27T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 27, 1951—5 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>617. <gloss target="#t_USTAC1">USTAC</gloss>. Just before delivery of our note to
                        <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> in London, Stephen Holmes invited
                    Corse and Lewis to have dinner tomorrow night with Harold Wilson, who is
                    arriving Torquay tomorrow.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 617, repeated information London 241.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Corse</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
